title: Inside the military base where Israeli troops train for expected ground assault on Gaza
description: A grid of narrow streets, framed by concrete apartment blocks and pro-Palestinian graffiti, is where Israeli troops are training in preparation for an expected ground assault on Gaza.

title: Italian priest wanted for murder and torture during Argentina's dictatorship to be extradited
description: An Italian priest sought by Argentina on charges of murder and torture during its last military dictatorship will be extradited, a lawyer has confirmed.

title: Recovered bodies show 'bloodthirsty' Hamas gunmen 'took their time over torture'
description: We've been travelling to the many different scenes where Hamas fighters carried out their terror attack on Israel this week, and it is becoming clear that their tactics and levels of brutality changed from location to location.

title: Netanyahu 'shouldn't' lead Israel in long run after country's 'most severe blow', ex-PM says
description: A former prime minister of Israel has said Benjamin Netanyahu should not remain the leader of the country in the long run after Hamas's unprecedented incursion.

title: Azerbaijani leader raises country's flag over former breakaway region
description: Azerbaijan's president has raised the national flag over the capital of the former breakaway region of Nagorno-Karabakh.

title: England through to Rugby World Cup semi-finals after victory over Fiji
description: England are through to the last four of the Rugby World Cup after a 30-24 victory over Fiji in their quarter-final in Marseille.

title: England v Fiji: Rugby World Cup quarter final LIVE
Venice mayor suspends electric buses after second crash follows overpass tragedy
description: The mayor of Venice has ordered an immediate stop to electric buses operated by La Linea after two crashes involving its vehicles - one of which led to the deaths of 21 people.

title: At least 30 dead and 167 missing after boat capsizes
description: At least 30 people have drowned and 167 are missing after a boat capsized on the Congo River in the Democratic Republic of the Congo.

title: 'Dad would be stoked': Steve Irwin's son breeds rare turtle named after late TV star
description: Robert Irwin, the son of the late conservationist Steve Irwin, has celebrated breeding a rare turtle named after his father.

title: Acclaimed Iranian film director and his wife stabbed to death in home
description: An award-winning Iranian film-maker and his wife have been stabbed to death in their home on the outskirts of Tehran, according to state media.

title: Voting in Poland under way as ruling populist party seeks to make history with third term in power
description: Voting has started in a Polish election with the ruling populist party seeking an unprecedented third term in power.

Britons trapped in Gaza will be supported, vows foreign secretary
description: Foreign Secretary James Cleverly has insisted the UK will maintain support for Britons trapped in Gaza, as he said it was proving "incredibly difficult" to open the Rafah border crossing into Egypt.

title: Madonna says suffering in Middle East 'heartbreaking' as delayed tour opens in London
description: Madonna has spoken of her heartbreak at the suffering in the Middle East as she kicked off her latest tour in London, which had been postponed following a life-threatening illness.

title: Afghanistan hit by third major earthquake in a week
description: Afghanistan has been hit by a 6.4 magnitude earthquake, its third in a week.

title: Israel preparing for 'coordinated offensive' in the Gaza Strip - as Iran pledges cooperation with Hamas
description: Israel is preparing to launch a "coordinated offensive" on the Gaza Strip, after the deadline given to Palestinians to move south to escape passed.
